---

## What "done" looks like

A successful project produces three artifacts at the project root:

| Artifact | Source | What it is |
|---|---|---|
| `model.orm.yaml` | Phases 1–3 | The conceptual ORM 2 model: object types, fact types, constraints, source provenance |
| `model.verbalization.txt` | Phase 4 | Halpin-style Controlled Natural Language verbalization of every fact type and constraint |
| `model.py` | Phase 5 | PyRel translation of the YAML, ready to load into RAI |

The `model.orm.yaml` is the source of truth. Verbalization and PyRel are derived from it.

---

## The skill behind this project

This project uses the `rai-orm-from-schema` skill (the SRP — Schema Recovery Procedure). The skill is loaded automatically when Claude Code starts in this directory. The phase plans (`.planning/phases/0N-*/PLAN.md`) tell the executor subagent which SRP steps to run per phase.

If the skill is missing, install it:

```bash
git clone -b an-orm-skill https://github.com/RelationalAI/rai-agent-skills ~/rai-skills
ln -s ~/rai-skills/skills/rai-orm-from-schema ~/.claude/skills/rai-orm-from-schema
```

---

## Scope boundary

- This project covers **recovery of an explicit data model** from an existing schema. It is not a greenfield modeling project — for that, use the text-flow (`bootstrap.sh --text`) which invokes the CSDP.
- This project does not refactor or migrate the underlying SQL schema. The output is a conceptual model that *describes* the schema; downstream systems decide what to do with it.
- This project does not include data migration, query rewriting, or runtime testing of PyRel against live data. Those are downstream.

---

## Stakeholders

| Role | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| Modeler (you) | Authors `/gsd:*` commands, reviews verbalizations, accepts/rejects proposed constraints. |
| Domain expert (optional) | Consulted at Phase 4 when the verifier surfaces ambiguous constraints. |
| Downstream consumer | Reads the final `model.py` and integrates into their RAI workload. |
